%%{init: {'theme': 'default', 'sequence': {'actorFontSize': 22, 'actorFontWeight': 'bold', 'messageFontSize': 20, 'noteFontSize': 18, 'mirrorActors': false, 'actorMargin': 60, 'boxMargin': 12, 'messageMargin': 40, 'wrap': true}}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor Court as Court User
    actor Ver as Verifier
    actor Admin as RSU Admin

    participant UI as nji-ui sitting module
    participant Sit as nji-sitting

    rect rgb(232, 240, 250)
        Note over Court,Sit: Phase 1 — List daily sittings awaiting confirmation
        Court->>UI: open Sittings, filter to yesterday and own office
        UI->>Sit: GET /v1/sittings?status=planned&office=...&date=...
        Sit-->>UI: list of planned sittings, auth-scoped
    end

    rect rgb(232, 250, 232)
        Note over Court,Sit: Phase 2 — Confirm with actual work type and AM/PM split per FR37, FR38
        Court->>UI: confirm a sitting and set actual work type
        UI->>Sit: POST /v1/sittings/{id}/confirm
        Sit->>Sit: validate, record actual work type, set status confirmed
        Sit-->>UI: 200 confirmed
        opt AM/PM split needed
            Court->>UI: split into AM and PM with different work types
            UI->>Sit: POST /v1/sittings/{id}/split
            Sit->>Sit: persist AM and PM rows, mark original superseded
            Sit-->>UI: 200 split
        end
    end

    rect rgb(250, 240, 230)
        Note over Court,Sit: Phase 3 — Verifier sign-off per FR40
        Note right of Ver: Verifier role is distinct from the confirmer per SIT-NFR-02.
        Ver->>UI: open Verifier view and select period
        UI->>Sit: POST /v1/sittings/verify?from=...&to=...&office=...
        Sit->>Sit: mark period as verified, sittings become read-only
        Sit-->>UI: 200 verified
    end

    rect rgb(250, 232, 240)
        Note over Court,Sit: Phase 4 — Post-verification re-open via RBAC-gated UI action
        Note right of Admin: At MVP the sitting re-open permission is granted to RSU Admin only. The re-opener must be different from the original confirmer per SIT-NFR-02 and from a standard Verifier. No external RFC process.
        Admin->>UI: open Re-open Verified Sitting screen, select sittings, enter mandatory justification
        UI->>Sit: POST /v1/sittings/{id}/re-open with justification body
        Sit->>Sit: check permission sitting:re-open via nji-authorisation
        Sit->>Sit: revert sittings from verified to confirmed
        Sit->>Sit: persist audit entry — who, when, justification, affected sittings
        Sit-->>UI: 200 re-opened
        UI-->>Admin: confirmation toast with audit reference
    end

    Note over Court,Sit: Confirmed and verified sittings are picked up by nji-payment-batch eligibility and by nji-itinerary / nji-mi-feed read federation.
